biomedical informatics for stanford medical students scholarly concentration biomedical informatics stanford medicine stanford school of medicine biomedical informatics search this site only stanford medical sites ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person stanford medical students can integrate biomedical informatics into their training the stanford medical curriculum provides medical training and an intellectual foundation which will support future medical investigation through the scholarly concentration stanford medical students must choose a scholarly concentration the concentration is split into 1 studies in one of eight foundation areas and 2 research in one of six application areas please note some of theses areas are extraordinarily broad biomedical informatics is a foundation area where students may choose to study biomedical informatics and apply what they have learned towards research in an application area the wide scope of biomedical informatics lends itself towards research in any of the application areas in addition students may use the scholarly concentration mechanism to initiate studies which culminate in a dual degree either the md ms or the md phd in biomedical informatics due to restrictions on our training grant the best funding mechanisms if you wish to enroll in the dual degree program are the medical scholars program and the medical scientist training program apply for the masters or phd after completing the md if you choose to complete the md first then apply for the masters or the phd in biomedical informatics within the restrictions of our grant you will be eligible for funding for both the masters and phd see the postdoctoral programs for more information about the obtaining the masters or the phd after completion of the md you are here current tab 4 stanford medicine school of medicine biomedical informatics for medical students navigation for this section prospective students overview graduate degrees du